'''Evgeny Gleizerov''' ({{lang-ru|<U+0415><U+0432><U+0433><U+0435><U+043D><U+0438><U+0439> <U+0413><U+043B><U+0435><U+0439><U+0437><U+0435><U+0440><U+043E><U+0432>}}; March 20, 1963) is a [[Russia]]n [[chess]] [[Grandmaster (chess)|Grandmaster]] (1993).

In 2001 he tied for 1st-3rd with [[Stanislav Voitsekhovsky]] and [[Michal Krasenkow]] at [[Barlinek]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://ratings.fide.com/tournament_report.phtml?event16=20263|title=IX Emanuela Laskera open A|publisher=FIDE|accessdate=5 May 2011}}</ref> He tied for 3rd-6th with [[David Berczes]], [[Yuriy Kuzubov]] and [[Pia Cramling]] in the Rilton Cup 2008/2009.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://ratings.fide.com/tournament_report.phtml?event16=17645|title=Rilton Cup 2008/2009|publisher=FIDE|accessdate=5 May 2011}}</ref> He came first at Parla [[2009]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://ratings.fide.com/tournament_report.phtml?event16=45199|title=XIV Campeonato de Parla 2009|publisher=FIDE|accessdate=5 May 2011}}</ref> In 2010 he tied for 1st-6th with [[Kamil Mito<U+0144>]], [[Bojan Kurajica]], [[Yuri Gonzalez Vidal]], [[L<U+00E1>zaro Bruz<U+00F3>n]] and [[Bartlomiej Heberla]] in the 4th Torneo Internacional de Ajedrez Ciudad de La Laguna.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.chessdom.com/news-2010/ajedrez-ciudad-de-la-laguna|title=Torneo Internacional de Ajedrez Ciudad de La Laguna|publisher=Chessdom.com|accessdate=5 May 2011}}</ref> In 2011 he tied for 1st-4th with [[Gadir Guseinov]], [[Merab Gagunashvili]] and [[Sergei Tiviakov]] in the 19th [[Fajr]] Open Chess Tournament.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://ratings.fide.com/tournament_report.phtml?event16=58700|title=19th Fajr International Open Chess Tournament|publisher=FIDE|accessdate=5 May 2011}}</ref>

